      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "TextEncodeQwenImageEditPlus",
        "cnr_id": "comfy-core",
        "ver": "0.3.76"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "EDIT PICTURE 1 into one completely new, coherent, edge-to-edge photograph. Picture 1 is the PRIMARY COMPOSITION ANCHOR: Stella riding her horse. Keep its single-scene photographic layout and use the horse, tack, and Stella's riding pose as the structural starting point, but create a new countryside moment and a new camera view. Picture 2 is Stella's IDENTITY REFERENCE ONLY: preserve her recognizable face, light hair, age, body proportions, and characteristic appearance; do not copy its background, framing, cap logo, nearby people, or selfie composition. Picture 3 is the DOG IDENTITY REFERENCE ONLY: preserve the dog's exact Weimaraner face, silver-brown coat, eyes, ears, collar, and body proportions; do not copy its sky, grass, portrait framing, or seated ground pose.\n\nThe final image is one uninterrupted full-frame scene from one camera: no collage, no mosaic, no split screen, no panels, no diptych, no triptych, no contact sheet, no borders, no frames, no inset pictures, and no visible source photos. Never place the three reference images next to each other. Use them only as visual identity and subject references.\n\nShow Stella and her dog riding together on the same horse along a safe countryside trail. The horse walks calmly. The dog sits naturally at the front of one correctly sized saddle, facing forward and balanced like a small first rider. Stella sits directly behind the dog, gently steadying it with one arm while correctly holding the reins with the other. Show exactly one Stella, exactly one dog, and exactly one horse. Show the complete horse from ears to hooves in a three-quarter side view, with both riders clearly visible. Make scale, contact points, limbs, paws, hands, reins, saddle, stirrups, lighting, and shadows physically plausible. Natural daylight, authentic photorealism, detailed skin, hair, fur, and tack, warm candid family mood. No duplicated people or animals, no detached portrait heads, no extra limbs, no merged bodies, no malformed anatomy, no text, no logo, no watermark."
      ],
      "color": "#1e3323",
      "bgcolor": "#36543d"
    },
